Five sailors committed suicide while serving with the Australian Navy on HMAS Stirling off the coast of Western Australia . 
  Their families did not know they had tried to take their own lives twice before . 
  The sailors were stationed at the same base for two years before their deaths . 
  Stuart Addison was best friends with Brett Dwyer who took his own life . 
  Jake Casey and Stephen Bebbington also committed suicide . 
  The families were kept in the dark about their drug use and depression . 
  A friend of Stuart said ice was the 'drug of choice in the Navy' The sailors served on the same ship and were stationed in the same area . 
 